title: Spider-Verse
body:
So I finally was able to see Into the Spider Verse last night. 

I LOVED IT. 

The animation? MIND-BLOWING
The soundtrack? FUCKING SUPERB, STILL LISTENING TO IT
The voice acting? 100% ON POINT

In conclusion: If you haven’t seen Spider Verse, YOU NEED TO. YOU WILL LOVE IT.

summary: I don't think there's any horror blogger on here like you who dabbles in the darkness. Also, and this is important: Seen any...
question: I don't think there's any horror blogger on here like you who dabbles in the darkness. Also, and this is important: Seen any superhero movies? Like the X-Men films or Sam Raimi's Spiderman?
answer:
Aw, thanks. To be honest, I’m not usually that into superhero movies. But here’s a list of DC and Marvel movies I’ve finished watching. 

  • The Amazing Spider-Man 2 (I started watching the first one then realized it didn’t have Dane DeHaan.)
  • The Avengers 
  • Batman Begins 
  • Blade (I couldn’t get into the second one.) 
  • Captain America: Civil War (I should watch Winter Soldier because I like Sebastian Stan…)
  • Captain America: The First Avenger  
  • The Dark Knight
  • The Dark Knight Rises
  • Deadpool
  • Deadpool 2
  • Ghost Rider (Wes Bentley’s character was the only reason I watched this.)
  • Guardians of the Galaxy
  • Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2 
  • Spider-Man: Homecoming (Tom Holland allegedly wore a th0ng under his Spidey suit. Allegedly.) 
  • Suicide Squad (This was a good flick, damn it.) 
  • Thor
  • Venom (GOOEY.) 
  • X-Men Apocalypse
  • X-Men: Days of Future Past (Quickpeters is bae.) 
  • X-Men: First Class

I want everyone who follows me to know this is my favorite version of Peter Parker.
